# Frontend Standards

## Framework

- React 19 with TypeScript strict mode
- Zustand for state management (no Redux)
- Tailwind CSS for styling (no CSS modules, no styled-components)
- Monaco Editor via `@monaco-editor/react` for code editing
- LiveKit via `@livekit/components-react` for video/audio
- MediaPipe via `@mediapipe/tasks-vision` for hand/face tracking

## Component Rules

- Functional components only — no class components
- One component per file, file name matches component name
- Props interfaces defined in the same file, named `{ComponentName}Props`
- Use custom hooks for logic reuse — prefix with `use`
- Colocate component-specific hooks in the same directory

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` in tsconfig — no exceptions
- No `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- All API response types defined in `frontend/src/types/`
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections

## State Management

- Zustand stores in `frontend/src/stores/`
- One store per domain (session, code, communication)
- Never put derived state in stores — compute it

## Accessibility (Critical for This Project)

- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- ARIA labels on all non-text elements
- Minimum contrast ratio 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
- Caption text must be configurable (size, font, background opacity)
